    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>Sunday 7h <hi rend="underline">Sep 1857</hi></date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">The Occident is at hand and I find<lb/> that I shall have to wait
                for the <date>October</date> No. before<lb/> my reply comes forth. You are the best
                judge in<lb/> these matters but it seems to me that provided you had<lb/> the time
                to get it up it would have been better if it <hi rend="underline">had<lb/>
                </hi>appeared at the same time as “O”=however you know<lb/> best and it might have
                    meditated<add>?</add> against you as a<lb/> journalist altho it is a query
                wither a proprietor of<lb/> a paper should allow a <sic>libellious</sic> article to
                appear<lb/> when he knows before hand that it is a libel—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have no copy of the refutation I sent you. Will<lb/> you oblige me
                with a <hi rend="underline">proof</hi> at your earliest convenience.<lb/> If I had
                had more time I could have answered on several<lb/> other points, which I think you
                might introduce into<lb/> your note or remarks—viz “<persName>C</persName>” starts
                with the intention<lb/> 1st of going by the “<hi rend="underline">record</hi>”...—he
                had the same <sic>opptunity</sic> of<lb/> referring to the record as I had—yet he
                does not bring<lb/> it forward as proof of his assertions,—he <hi rend="underline"
                    >positively deceives</hi><lb/> you into publishing a libel on <hi
                    rend="underline">me</hi>. I bring the record</p>
            <p>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> Elements of Jewish faith is a deception should<lb/> have been
                Elements of <persName>Poznanskis</persName> faithessness”</p>
            <p>3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi>
                <persName>S.N.C</persName> neither <hi rend="underline">painted beautiful
                    pictures</hi><lb/> or <hi rend="underline">portraits</hi>
                <del>of</del> from imagination, he only <del>gave</del> prevented<lb/> a <hi
                    rend="underline">daguerreotype</hi> verso of things as they really are</p>
            <p>4 <persName>C </persName>refers to the Trustees for the truth of his assertion<lb/>
                about the creed—and says the Prest <persName>Mr Olloing <add>?</add></persName></p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>at that time was on the committee this is false<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. O.</persName> was not, the board consisted of</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Ollolengrin<add>?</add></persName> Prest <persName>Josh
                    Lazarus</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName>J. C. Levy</persName>
                <persName>Sol Moses</persName>
                <persName>Js Woolff</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Abraham Moise</persName>, and <persName>Isaih
                    Moses</persName>, and at<lb/> that time no reform was thought of, with the<lb/>
                exception of the organ—<persName>Poznanski</persName> ought to have<lb/> made a
                reform “ten Commandments,” at same time<lb/> “Extract of a letter from
                    <persName>Poznanski </persName>to <persName>Dr. Eckman</persName><lb/> dated
                    <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>Apl 29. 5610</date></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">“The doctrine of a personal Messiah is generally<lb/> regarded as
                unfounded <add>by our congregation</add> and as a sound of evil<lb/> to the Jewish
                Nation.”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">This goes to prove that “<persName>C</persName>” makes a fool<lb/>
                of himself when he speaks of <persName>Dr. E.</persName> touching gratuitously<lb/>
                on the <hi rend="underline">vital</hi> principle of the Messiah, or that it<lb/> is
                done to deceive the unwary. You can use the<lb/> quotation above. I copied it from
                the Original.—</p>
            <p><persName>C</persName> was told (the day the Proof was recd) by <persName>Mr.
                    Moise</persName><lb/> and <persName>Mr Valentine</persName> that his assertions
                were false<lb/> that <persName>S N C</persName> could bring Documents to prove his
                assertions.<lb/> Yet he did not suppress it altho he had two<lb/> weeks to do it in,
                — and the records to examine or refer to,<lb/> the result has been that the
                Jewish<lb/> party have ceased going to Synagogue as the<lb/> creed a la
                        <persName><sic>Piznasty</sic></persName>—is sh<add>?</add> in the
                walls—<lb/> yesterday <persName>Dr E</persName> had 4 members in Synagogue.</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>your remarks are the admiration of every body<lb/> you hail “<persName>C</persName>”
                as a firm believer in the faith”<lb/>
                <persName>Mr N Levin</persName> told me he could prove by s<add>?</add>e
                gentleman<lb/> that <persName>Isaac Cardoza</persName> exposed himself before him
                and<lb/> the s<add>?</add>e persons that he did not believe in the bible”<lb/>—this
                is nothing to me but <persName>Mr C.</persName> better take care<lb/> how he becomes
                personal, he lives in open concubinage<lb/> with a <sic>mullato</sic> woman by whom
                he had six<lb/> illegitimate children, and to this day is running<lb/> after colored
                girls—it is shameful for such a<lb/> man to insinuate about professors of
                Religion<lb/> going into p<add>?</add> of <hi rend="underline">vice</hi>—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I wrote you requesting as a favor that you<lb/> would reply
                immediately to me but I suppose<lb/> business prevented<add>?</add>—if you can
                manage to<lb/> send me an early <del>poof</del> proof I would feel much<lb/> obliged
                as it might require some alteration<lb/> or amendment—give my kind regards to<lb/>
                <persName>S. S.</persName> and family.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The article of <persName>Mr Wise</persName> is impertinent<lb/> in
                the extreme—he has proved himself a<lb/> rain man. 20 years hence, the world
                will<lb/> become so enlightened that he will get justice<lb/> done him—in mean time
                let us consign<lb/> him to obscurity.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours Sincerely</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">J N Carvalho</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. I Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Phi</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">turn over</p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p>P. S. Please expunge from <persName>Dr Eckmans</persName> letter<lb/> to you the
                sentence <hi rend="underline">about founders of the</hi><lb/> congregation. let it
                only speak of the Conversation<lb/> between <persName>P</persName> &amp;
                    <persName>Dr. E.</persName>—you will arrange it so<lb/> that it reads
                correctly—and any improvement<lb/> you wish to make in mine you <del>Bar F</del>
                have<lb/> my permission. <persName>Dr. E.</persName> request me to<lb/> say that he
                wished the above sentence erased.</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Yours tr <persName role="author">J N</persName></p>
            <p>
                <del>I give the report of the following in <persName>Dr. E</persName> own words<lb/>
                    Last year after <date>Kipur</date>
                    <del>when</del> at the time <persName>Dr<lb/> E.</persName> Denounced
                        <persName>Poz</persName> as greatly of infidelity &amp;
                        hypocritiscy<add>?</add> his friends<lb/> wanted satisfaction, <del>and
                        called</del> and prepared a paper stating<lb/> that the <persName>Rev S
                        Poznanski</persName> believed in the bible and<lb/> they obtained about 25
                    signatures to it.—<persName>Dr. E.</persName><lb/> friends wanted that he should
                    to <del>make</del> compose matters<lb/> also give <persName>Mr P</persName> a
                            <del><add>?</add></del> paper to the purpose that <persName>Dr
                        E</persName> should take <persName>P</persName> word that he believe in the
                    bible but he refused<lb/>—this goes to prove that such a denouncement<lb/> took
                    place. which “<persName>C</persName>” Denies,—or why should<lb/> it be necessary
                    for <persName>Mr P.</persName> to obtain a certificate that<lb/> he believes in
                    the bible.—how is it possible<lb/> for any body to know what I
                    believe?<lb/></del>
            </p>
        </body>
